feat: opt-in background plugin-update check + sidebar badge

Adds the daily plugin-update check from the roadmap, with one
deliberate departure from the original spec: it is **opt-in**, not
opt-out. The default-OFF posture keeps air-gapped and
privacy-sensitive installs quiet by default — no outbound calls to
nuget.org happen until an operator explicitly flips
Bowire:PluginUpdateCheck:Enabled=true (or passes --update-check on
the standalone tool).

Server side
  src/Kuestenlogik.Bowire/Plugins/
    PluginUpdateCheckService.cs        — pulls latest stable / pre
                                         versions of each installed
                                         sibling plugin from
                                         nuget.org v3-flatcontainer;
                                         persists snapshot to
                                         ~/.bowire/state/update-check.json
    PluginUpdateCheckHostedService.cs  — BackgroundService that runs
                                         the check on startup + every
                                         IntervalHours when opted-in;
                                         short-circuits with a
                                         LogDebug when disabled.
    BowirePluginUpdateCheckOptions     — Enabled/IntervalHours/
                                         IncludePrerelease, bound to
                                         Bowire:PluginUpdateCheck via
                                         the standard options pipeline.

  Endpoints/BowirePluginEndpoints.cs
    GET /api/plugins/check-updates        — manual on-demand check
                                            (always available — a
                                            direct user action is not
                                            gated by the opt-in).
    GET /api/plugins/check-updates/status — read the persisted cache
                                            + opt-in state; powers
                                            the sidebar badge without
                                            re-hitting the network.

  BowireServiceCollectionExtensions.cs
    Registers PluginUpdateCheckService (always) + the hosted service
    + AddOptions().BindConfiguration("Bowire:PluginUpdateCheck").

CLI
  src/Kuestenlogik.Bowire.Tool/Cli/BowireCli.cs
